an Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Gorenflos","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Ewald.","German: from French <b>Gorenflos</b>, a habitational name from Gorenflos in Somme, France. <i>Gorenflo</i> is a Huguenot name, originally from Friedrichstal (founded by Huguenots), now Stutensee, near Karlsruhe (Baden-Württemberg). See also   Colliflower  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Colliflower","meanings":["Altered form of German   Gorenflo  , a surname of French origin.","History: Georg Adam Goranflo (actually <i>Gorenflo</i>) arrived in Philadelphia, PA, on the ship <i>Ann</i> in 1749 and settled in Hagerstown, MD, the name being changed to <i>Colliflower</i> in the process. His forebear Jacques de Gorenflos was a leading Huguenot in the 17th century. Religious persecution drove the family to Germany, where their surname became <i>Gorenflo</i>, and from there Georg Adam Goranflo emigrated to North America."]}]},{"name":"Hugues","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Hugues Capet  (  ?938–96 ) was ruler of France (  987–96 ) and founder of the Capetian dynasty.  See  <b>Hugh</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Hugues de Gorenflos was born in 1190, his father, Hugues de Gorenflos, was 31 and his mother, Mathilde de Bernatre, was 19. He had at least 1 daughter with Havoise de Drucat. He died in 1254, at the age of 64."},"et":{"1190–1254":"1190–1254","1198–1257":"1198–1257","1232–1289":"1232–1289","1159–1218":"1159–1218","1171–1237":"1171–1237","1190":"1190","1237":"1237","1159":"11